Ye interview me bahut pucha jata hai:

Q. filter() kis Functional Interface ka use karta hai?

Answer:

Predicate<T>


⭐ filter() — Most Important Stream Operation

filter() Collection me se sirf wahi elements select karta hai jo kisi condition ko satisfy karte hain.

Simple definition:

Collection
      ↓
filter(condition)
      ↓
Sirf matching data
Real Life Example

Maan lo class me 10 students hain.

Rahul   - 35 Marks
Vijay   - 90 Marks
Aman    - 20 Marks
Rohit   - 80 Marks

Ab teacher bolta hai:

"Sirf PASS students dikhao."

Result:

Vijay - 90
Rohit - 80

Yehi kaam filter() karta hai.

Syntax
stream.filter(predicate)

Sabse important baat:

filter() ke andar Predicate<T> lagta hai.

Yaad hai?

Predicate<Integer> isAdult =
        age -> age >= 18;

Same concept yahan use hota hai.